    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Then the Levite, the husband of the murdered woman, described the whole affair. הגּבעה בּעלי, the owners or citizens of Gibeah (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 9:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). \"Me they intended to kill:\" the Levite draws this conclusion from what had happened to his wife; the men of Gibeah had not expressed any such intention in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 19:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"All the country (lit. field) of the inheritance of Israel,\" i.e., all the land of the Israelites. זמּה is applied to the vice of lewdness, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 18:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which was to be punished with death. וגו לכם הבוּ, \"give yourselves (לכם as dat. comm.) word and counsel here,\" i.e., make up your minds and pass sentence (vid., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
